<TITLE> WC prosecutor warns against obstruction </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 1(bdnews24.com)The war crime prosecutor has said that anyone who hinders its investigation into 1971 war crimes or threatens any witness, will be arrested. Golam Arif Tipu was talking to reporters at his office in the old High Court Building on Thursday. He said, "If any person who is accused of a war crimes offence, and does anything to hinder the task of the investigation body he will be put behind bars." Arif said that he had talks with the tribunal chairman over provisions of the law to try the culprits. Asked how offences will be proved, he said, "Many people witnessed mass killings, torture on women, arson and plundering and their statements will help a lot in proving the offence." In addition, many victims are still alive and they will be vital witness, he said adding that newspapers and books published during that period would also be used. bdn
